    "After using SBDD to improve compound 10 further, researchers isolated the macrocyclic inhibitor QR-6401.",
    "An IC50 of 0.46 nM was observed for QR-6401, indicating that it is highly active and selective against CDK2.",
    "The anti-cancer activity and oral bioavailability in an OVCAR3 ovarian cancer xenograft model were similarly promising.",
    "By combining generative models with SBDD, the scientists found that they could speed up finding novel medications.",
    "With QR-6401 as a proof-of-concept, generative models and SBDD are expected to be employed to find other effective drugs (Ren et al., 2023)."
